## DB Schema Changes Required

The current [schema.sql](file:///c:/Users/Youssef/Documents/Uni/Software/Semester%201/Project/Implementation/JavaApplication6/src/main/resources/db/schema.sql) only has 3 tables. The following **4 new tables** are needed:

```sql
-- Transfer Table
CREATE TABLE [Transfer] (
    transfer_id   INT IDENTITY(1,1) PRIMARY KEY,
    from_account  NVARCHAR(50) NOT NULL REFERENCES [Account](account_number),
    to_account    NVARCHAR(50) NOT NULL REFERENCES [Account](account_number),
    amount        DECIMAL(18,2) NOT NULL,
    timestamp     DATETIME2 DEFAULT SYSDATETIME(),
    reference_code NVARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
    status        NVARCHAR(50) DEFAULT 'COMPLETED'
);

-- Loan Table
CREATE TABLE [Loan] (
    loan_id        INT IDENTITY(1,1) PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id    INT NOT NULL REFERENCES [Customer](customer_id),
    amount         DECIMAL(18,2) NOT NULL,
    loan_type      NVARCHAR(50),
    duration_months INT,
    purpose        NVARCHAR(500),
    status         NVARCHAR(50) DEFAULT 'PENDING',
    submission_date DATETIME2 DEFAULT SYSDATETIME(),
    decision_date  DATETIME2
);

-- InterestPosting Table
CREATE TABLE [InterestPosting] (
    posting_id     INT IDENTITY(1,1) PRIMARY KEY,
    account_number NVARCHAR(50) NOT NULL REFERENCES [Account](account_number),
    amount         DECIMAL(18,2) NOT NULL,
    timestamp      DATETIME2 DEFAULT SYSDATETIME(),
    rate_used      DECIMAL(8,6) NOT NULL
);

-- OverdraftEvent Table
CREATE TABLE [OverdraftEvent] (
    overdraft_id   INT IDENTITY(1,1) PRIMARY KEY,
    account_number NVARCHAR(50) NOT NULL REFERENCES [Account](account_number),
    transaction_id INT REFERENCES [Transactions](transaction_id),
    timestamp      DATETIME2 DEFAULT SYSDATETIME(),
    amount         DECIMAL(18,2) NOT NULL,
    alert_sent     BIT DEFAULT 0
);
```

---

## Recommended Implementation Order

> [!TIP]
> Implement in this order to minimize dependency blockers (each use case builds on the previous ones).

| Priority | Use Case | Rationale |
|----------|----------|-----------|
| 1 | **UC-03** Create Customer Profile | No new tables needed; unlocks self-registration |
| 2 | **UC-05** Deposit Cash | Core banking operation; needs `AccountDAO.updateBalance()` + `TransactionDAO.insert()` which are reused by all later UCs |
| 3 | **UC-06** Withdraw Cash | Reuses deposit infrastructure; adds fund-check logic |
| 4 | **UC-13** Overdraft Alert | Natural extension of withdrawal; adds the [OverdraftEvent](file:///c:/Users/Youssef/Documents/Uni/Software/Semester%201/Project/Implementation/JavaApplication6/src/main/java/com/bms/domain/entity/OverdraftEvent.java#8-101) table |
| 5 | **UC-07** Transfer Funds | Combines deposit + withdrawal + adds [Transfer](file:///c:/Users/Youssef/Documents/Uni/Software/Semester%201/Project/Implementation/JavaApplication6/src/main/java/com/bms/domain/entity/Transfer.java#8-113) table |
| 6 | **UC-08** Update Account Status | Simple admin feature; no new tables |
| 7 | **UC-09** Apply for Loan | Adds [Loan](file:///c:/Users/Youssef/Documents/Uni/Software/Semester%201/Project/Implementation/JavaApplication6/src/main/java/com/bms/domain/entity/Loan.java#8-69) table; independent of transfer/deposit |
| 8 | **UC-10** Review Loan | Extends UC-09; admin operation |
| 9 | **UC-11** View Loan Status | Read-only; depends on UC-09 data |
| 10 | **UC-12** Monthly Interest | Batch operation; adds [InterestPosting](file:///c:/Users/Youssef/Documents/Uni/Software/Semester%201/Project/Implementation/JavaApplication6/src/main/java/com/bms/domain/entity/InterestPosting.java#8-53) table; can be done last |

